<i>âªMy world is with my girlsâª</i>

00:01:09.969 --> 00:01:12.272 line:95%,end
<i>âªLivin' on the dance floorâª</i>

00:01:13.373 --> 00:01:16.609 line:5%,start
(dramatic music playing)

00:01:16.676 --> 00:01:18.011 line:5%,start
ABBY: <i>Ladies! Let's go!</i>

00:01:18.078 --> 00:01:18.912 line:5%,start
<i>Come on!</i>

00:01:18.978 --> 00:01:20.213 line:95%,end
We have lots to go over.

00:01:20.280 --> 00:01:22.682 line:95%,end
It's going to be a busy,
busy, busy week here.

00:01:22.749 --> 00:01:23.750 line:95%,end
No coming late,

00:01:23.817 --> 00:01:25.051 line:95%,end
no leaving early.

00:01:25.618 --> 00:01:27.854 line:95%,end
Now, Texas.

00:01:28.988 --> 00:01:31.224 line:95%,end
We had all these plans made

00:01:31.291 --> 00:01:32.425 line:95%,end
to go to New Jersey.

00:01:32.492 --> 00:01:34.227 line:95%,end
And then, at the last minute,

00:01:34.294 --> 00:01:35.695 line:95%,end
we have to completely flip it.

00:01:35.762 --> 00:01:37.664 line:95%,end
There's a lot of dance companies
in this country

00:01:37.730 --> 00:01:39.799 line:95%,end
that would have said,
"Fine, we're not going."

00:01:39.866 --> 00:01:41.234 line:95%,end
And we didn't do that. We went,

00:01:41.301 --> 00:01:42.836 line:95%,end
some great things happened

00:01:42.902 --> 00:01:45.638 line:95%,end
and some really bad
things happened.

00:01:47.006 --> 00:01:48.942 line:95%,end
Now, this week,

00:01:49.008 --> 00:01:50.944 line:95%,end
we are going to Hollywood Vibe

00:01:51.010 --> 00:01:52.545 line:95%,end
right here in Pittsburgh.

00:01:53.179 --> 00:01:54.147 line:95%,end
(applause)

00:01:54.214 --> 00:01:57.217 line:95%,end
I want to see 100%
from every single one of you.

00:01:57.283 --> 00:01:59.619 line:95%,end
Remember, we're in our backyard.

00:01:59.686 --> 00:02:01.754 line:95%,end
You have a target on your back,

00:02:01.821 --> 00:02:03.056 line:95%,end
so do I.

00:02:03.123 --> 00:02:06.860 line:95%,end
<i>There's a little bit more riding</i>
<i>on Hollywood Vibe</i>

00:02:06.926 --> 00:02:09.162 line:5%,start
because it's in
Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.

00:02:09.229 --> 00:02:11.931 line:95%,end
The group number is
called "Private Eyes."

00:02:12.565 --> 00:02:14.801 line:95%,end
I'm going to arm you
with the secret weapon.

00:02:15.869 --> 00:02:17.904 line:95%,end
You're going to be using guns...

00:02:17.971 --> 00:02:19.739 line:95%,end
-(dramatic effect)
-ABBY: ...in your routine.

00:02:19.806 --> 00:02:21.341 line:95%,end
When you step on that stage,

00:02:21.407 --> 00:02:22.942 line:95%,end
I want you to kill it.

00:02:23.009 --> 00:02:23.843 line:95%,end
Understood?

00:02:23.910 --> 00:02:26.045 line:95%,end
You're going to blow
the competition away.

00:02:26.112 --> 00:02:27.981 line:5%,start
I'm not really
thrilled at the idea

00:02:28.047 --> 00:02:30.383 line:5%,start
of my daughter dancing on stage
with a weapon.

00:02:30.450 --> 00:02:32.752 line:95%,end
Plastic or not, it's still
sending the wrong message.

00:02:32.819 --> 00:02:35.622 line:95%,end
But I'm so used to sending
the wrong message at Abby's,

00:02:35.688 --> 00:02:37.023 line:95%,end
I should really just...

00:02:37.891 --> 00:02:39.025 line:95%,end
I should give up.

00:02:39.092 --> 00:02:40.593 line:95%,end
Now, we're going to
move into the pyramid.

00:02:41.161 --> 00:02:42.562 line:95%,end
Mackenzie...

00:02:42.629 --> 00:02:45.398 line:95%,end
you went from first to worst

00:02:45.465 --> 00:02:46.833 line:95%,end
in one routine.

00:02:47.233 --> 00:02:49.369 line:95%,end
You always have to keep working.

00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:52.372 line:95%,end
Nia, you had a pretty dance.

00:02:52.438 --> 00:02:53.706 line:95%,end
I thought you did well.

00:02:53.773 --> 00:02:54.908 line:95%,end
No problem.

00:02:56.476 --> 00:02:57.544 line:95%,end
Kendall...

00:02:57.610 --> 00:02:59.379 line:95%,end
I understand the
costume was an issue...

00:02:59.445 --> 00:03:00.780 line:95%,end
This is Kendall's costume.

00:03:00.847 --> 00:03:02.949 line:95%,end
They don't need a
$500 costume to win.

00:03:03.016 --> 00:03:05.318 line:95%,end
I'm sick of this (bleep)!

00:03:05.385 --> 00:03:07.387 line:95%,end
ABBY: Jill, I'm sure you have
something to say about it,

00:03:07.453 --> 00:03:08.621 line:95%,end
but I'll tell you what--

00:03:08.688 --> 00:03:10.256 line:95%,end
it doesn't matter what you wear.

00:03:10.323 --> 00:03:12.058 line:95%,end
Ultimately, at the
end of the day,

00:03:12.125 --> 00:03:12.959 line:95%,end
it's your technique.

00:03:13.026 --> 00:03:14.494 line:95%,end
That's what you need to work on.

00:03:15.228 --> 00:03:18.064 line:95%,end
All right. Next, Maddie.

00:03:18.131 --> 00:03:19.265 line:95%,end
(dramatic effect)

00:03:20.500 --> 00:03:22.702 line:95%,end
Maddie, you could have been
seriously injured.

00:03:22.769 --> 00:03:25.805 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:03:28.374 --> 00:03:29.842 line:95%,end
ABBY: Get the pout
off your face, Maddie.

00:03:29.909 --> 00:03:31.644 line:95%,end
You know that you
made that mistake,

00:03:31.711 --> 00:03:32.946 line:95%,end
and that's what you get.

00:03:33.446 --> 00:03:35.381 line:95%,end
JILL: <i>I don't feel that Maddie</i>
<i>should be at the bottom</i>

00:03:35.448 --> 00:03:36.583 line:95%,end
<i>of the pyramid this week.</i>

00:03:36.649 --> 00:03:37.684 line:95%,end
<i>I think it's ridiculous.</i>

00:03:37.750 --> 00:03:39.452 line:5%,start
She fell, things happen,

00:03:39.519 --> 00:03:42.555 line:5%,start
and I'm just glad my
daughter's not hurt.

00:03:43.456 --> 00:03:45.291 line:95%,end
ABBY: So let that be a lesson
to everybody.

00:03:45.358 --> 00:03:47.393 line:95%,end
Don't change your
mind in midair.

00:03:47.460 --> 00:03:48.661 line:95%,end
Moving on.

00:03:48.728 --> 00:03:49.596 line:95%,end
Chloe.

00:03:50.029 --> 00:03:51.664 line:95%,end
Chloe, it was good,

00:03:51.731 --> 00:03:53.499 line:95%,end
but obviously not good enough.

00:03:53.566 --> 00:03:55.501 line:95%,end
Next, I have Brooke.

00:03:55.568 --> 00:03:56.703 line:95%,end
Great performance,

00:03:56.769 --> 00:03:58.204 line:95%,end
and then forgot the ending.

00:03:58.271 --> 00:04:00.540 line:95%,end
You didn't know what you were
doing and you just fizzled out.

00:04:00.607 --> 00:04:02.108 line:95%,end
And on the top of the pyramid...

00:04:02.976 --> 00:04:04.410 line:95%,end
-Paige.
-(squealing)

00:04:04.477 --> 00:04:06.179 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:04:06.246 --> 00:04:07.347 line:95%,end
ABBY: Paige, your
legs were straight.

00:04:07.413 --> 00:04:08.615 line:95%,end
Your feet were pointed.

00:04:08.681 --> 00:04:09.849 line:95%,end
And you went out
there and you won it.

00:04:09.916 --> 00:04:11.784 line:95%,end
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

00:04:11.851 --> 00:04:13.586 line:95%,end
KELLY: <i>I think</i>
<i>everybody in the room</i>

00:04:13.653 --> 00:04:16.422 line:5%,start
just wanted to, like,
jump up and down for Paige.
(laughs)

00:04:16.489 --> 00:04:18.591 line:95%,end
She has never been
at the top of the pyramid,

00:04:18.658 --> 00:04:20.526 line:95%,end
<i>and she really deserves this.</i>

00:04:21.394 --> 00:04:23.329 line:95%,end
All right, ladies,
the group number,

00:04:23.396 --> 00:04:25.131 line:95%,end
everyone will be dancing

00:04:25.198 --> 00:04:26.799 line:95%,end
except Mackenzie.

00:04:26.866 --> 00:04:28.735 line:95%,end
I'm going to enter a trio...

00:04:30.336 --> 00:04:33.906 line:95%,end
Chloe, Maddie, and...

00:04:36.542 --> 00:04:37.510 line:95%,end
Paige.

00:04:38.711 --> 00:04:40.313 line:95%,end
I'm going to pick you
back into the trio

00:04:40.380 --> 00:04:41.681 line:95%,end
because you're on
top of the pyramid.

00:04:42.348 --> 00:04:43.716 line:95%,end
Kendall...

00:04:43.783 --> 00:04:44.817 line:95%,end
get the look on your face.

00:04:44.884 --> 00:04:46.819 line:95%,end
I can't take any
chances this week.

00:04:46.886 --> 00:04:49.355 line:95%,end
I need to win.

00:04:49.422 --> 00:04:51.357 line:95%,end
JILL: <i>Kendall and I</i>
<i>decide to stick this out.</i>

00:04:51.424 --> 00:04:53.092 line:95%,end
<i>We want to make this work.</i>

00:04:53.159 --> 00:04:54.927 line:95%,end
<i>We are team players.</i>

00:04:54.994 --> 00:04:56.129 line:5%,start
So we come back,

00:04:56.195 --> 00:04:57.463 line:5%,start
we're part of the team,


00:04:57.530 --> 00:04:59.632 line:5%,start
and this is how Abby repays us--

00:04:59.699 --> 00:05:01.668 line:95%,end
by taking Kendall
out of the trio.

00:05:01.734 --> 00:05:02.669 line:95%,end
Chloe...

00:05:02.735 --> 00:05:03.936 line:95%,end
you will be doing a solo.

00:05:04.003 --> 00:05:05.705 line:95%,end
Maddie, you will
be doing a solo.

00:05:05.772 --> 00:05:07.206 line:95%,end
We're taking two champions

00:05:07.273 --> 00:05:08.908 line:95%,end
that already won
at Hollywood Vibe.

00:05:09.409 --> 00:05:11.577 line:95%,end
I'm telling you,
one of you better with it again.

00:05:11.644 --> 00:05:13.212 line:95%,end
-Do you understand?
-GIRLS: Yes.

00:05:13.279 --> 00:05:15.715 line:95%,end
I want to see that
champion in the studio.

00:05:16.382 --> 00:05:17.283 line:95%,end
You're dismissed.

00:05:17.350 --> 00:05:18.785 line:95%,end
-Thank you.
-GIRLS: Thank you.

00:05:18.851 --> 00:05:20.019 line:95%,end
No. You guys spread apart.

00:05:20.086 --> 00:05:21.020 line:95%,end
Let's go.

00:05:21.087 --> 00:05:23.556 line:5%,start
(upbeat music playing)

00:05:24.524 --> 00:05:26.693 line:5%,start
Girls, This is Hollywood Vibe.

00:05:26.759 --> 00:05:28.661 line:5%,start
The last time you
did your group there,

00:05:28.728 --> 00:05:29.595 line:5%,start
you didn't win.

00:05:29.662 --> 00:05:30.830 line:95%,end
It was embarrassing.

00:05:30.897 --> 00:05:32.899 line:95%,end
<i>The group number is</i>
<i>called </i>Private Eyes.

00:05:32.965 --> 00:05:34.300 line:95%,end
Every so many years,

00:05:34.367 --> 00:05:36.669 line:95%,end
I do some type of Dick Tracy,

00:05:36.736 --> 00:05:38.805 line:95%,end
private eye, "Charlie's Angels,"

00:05:38.871 --> 00:05:40.106 line:95%,end
something-something.

00:05:40.173 --> 00:05:43.376 line:95%,end
But I wanted to make
it a little edgier,

00:05:43.443 --> 00:05:45.845 line:95%,end
so guns.

00:05:45.912 --> 00:05:47.980 line:95%,end
I need--I need spies.

00:05:48.047 --> 00:05:50.216 line:95%,end
I need detectives.

00:05:50.283 --> 00:05:52.685 line:95%,end
Well, I'm sure hoping that
they're using just their fingers
as guns,

00:05:52.752 --> 00:05:54.220 line:95%,end
because I know those--

00:05:54.287 --> 00:05:55.455 line:95%,end
<i>I know we're not allowed</i>
<i>to use those guns.</i>

00:05:55.521 --> 00:05:57.623 line:95%,end
-Just like you said, they are
not allowed. -It is written--

00:05:57.690 --> 00:05:59.292 line:95%,end
I don't think we should allow
them to use guns.

00:05:59.359 --> 00:06:00.493 line:95%,end
-Absolutely. I think at some
point... -No.

00:06:00.560 --> 00:06:01.461 line:95%,end
...we just need to
put our foot down.

00:06:02.261 --> 00:06:04.330 line:95%,end
<i>I don't have a</i>
<i>problem with the gun</i>

00:06:04.397 --> 00:06:05.365 line:95%,end
or that idea.

00:06:05.431 --> 00:06:06.966 line:95%,end
I don't think little girl
should be dancing

00:06:07.033 --> 00:06:08.468 line:95%,end
around on stage with
guns in their hands.

00:06:08.534 --> 00:06:10.136 line:95%,end
-CHRISTI: I agree with that.
-I think we do have some
standards here.

00:06:10.203 --> 00:06:11.337 line:95%,end
-MELISSA: <i>Yes.</i>
-HOLLY: <i>And they shouldn't be</i>
<i>doing that.</i>

00:06:11.404 --> 00:06:12.672 line:95%,end
-Oh, teach my kid to use guns.
-You're going to blow

00:06:12.739 --> 00:06:14.340 line:95%,end
the competition away.

00:06:14.407 --> 00:06:15.908 line:95%,end
-Yeah. Blow the competition and
kill. -(overlapping chatter)

00:06:15.975 --> 00:06:17.443 line:95%,end
If you can't beat
'em, shoot 'em.

00:06:17.510 --> 00:06:18.611 line:95%,end
That doesn't--yeah.

00:06:18.678 --> 00:06:20.246 line:95%,end
That doesn't sound
like "Charlie's Angels."

00:06:20.313 --> 00:06:22.315 line:95%,end
1 and 2, and 3, and...

00:06:23.950 --> 00:06:25.818 line:95%,end
So I'm glad Paige
is back in the trio.

00:06:26.719 --> 00:06:28.354 line:95%,end
-I am, too.
-I know.

00:06:28.421 --> 00:06:30.356 line:95%,end
JILL: I don't understand why.

00:06:30.423 --> 00:06:32.058 line:95%,end
I thought for sure

00:06:32.125 --> 00:06:33.659 line:95%,end
she was going to put
Kendall back in it.

00:06:33.726 --> 00:06:35.862 line:95%,end
Paige was at the top
of the pyramid this week.

00:06:35.928 --> 00:06:37.397 line:95%,end
-MELISSA: That's why.
-She should be doing a solo.

00:06:37.463 --> 00:06:39.298 line:95%,end
Not just a trio,
She should be doing a solo.

00:06:39.365 --> 00:06:40.900 line:95%,end
She's at the top of the pyramid.

00:06:40.967 --> 00:06:42.869 line:95%,end
Jill's a little upset
that the Kendall's not in the
trio.

00:06:42.935 --> 00:06:45.738 line:95%,end
But when Kendall
was in the trio and Paige
wasn't,

00:06:45.805 --> 00:06:48.541 line:95%,end
<i>Jill couldn't understand</i>
<i>why Kelly would be upset about</i>
<i>anything.</i>

00:06:48.608 --> 00:06:51.677 line:95%,end
So, Jill, what's good for the
goose is good for the gander.

00:06:51.744 --> 00:06:54.147 line:95%,end
I'm feeling pretty
left out for my child,

00:06:54.213 --> 00:06:56.616 line:95%,end
who has been here
since she was three.

00:06:56.682 --> 00:06:57.817 line:95%,end
And she's never had a trio.

00:06:57.884 --> 00:06:59.585 line:95%,end
Holly, maybe if you were here
more often...

00:06:59.652 --> 00:07:00.486 line:95%,end
(Christi gasps)

00:07:00.553 --> 00:07:03.923 line:95%,end
...and Abby thought you were
more a part of us in the team,

00:07:03.990 --> 00:07:05.758 line:95%,end
maybe she would get more parts.

00:07:05.825 --> 00:07:07.093 line:95%,end
I just don't want
to pay extra for it.

00:07:07.160 --> 00:07:08.661 line:95%,end
But, yes, I want my
child to feel good.

00:07:08.728 --> 00:07:09.829 line:95%,end
(Christi chuckles)

00:07:10.263 --> 00:07:11.130 line:95%,end
See where you are?

00:07:11.197 --> 00:07:12.465 line:95%,end
Now go back.

00:07:12.532 --> 00:07:15.568 line:95%,end
Jill, it looks like Kendall is
getting a special little part in
there.

00:07:16.002 --> 00:07:17.236 line:95%,end
So you ought to be
happy about that.

00:07:17.303 --> 00:07:18.404 line:95%,end
Then pat me on the back.

00:07:18.471 --> 00:07:19.539 line:95%,end
Maybe I'm doing something right.

